&lt;p&gt;Ambulatory Emergency Care Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic Band 5 Registered Nurse to join our Ambulatory Emergency Care (AEC) team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AEC takes referrals from our Emergency Department and from GP surgeries to provide same day emergency care and prevent hospital admission wherever possible. You will have the opportunity to provide care for a variety of illnesses and develop your nursing skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AEC is open 7 days a week and runs from 8am -10pm. You will be part of a team of RN’s, CSW’s and Clerk’s and you will be expected to be flexible with your working patterns. You will need to be competent in phlebotomy and cannulation and recording ECG’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to come and meet the team or would like further information regarding this exciting opportunity please contact Senior Sister Kelly Saville on extension 7575.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
